<br>
Well this is just one aspect to RL, and I do mean Real Life.  If you have ever played a game of minesweeper at work to pass the time or challenge your mind... then EQ is similar in many aspects.<br>
<br>
Now ANYTHING taken to excess is a bad thing.  Balance is what people need in life.  For me, I do play a lot of EQ, but I am also working 50 hrs a week at my engineering job, taking 2 master's courses each semester, train for marathons and have time for a significant other from time to time.  Now, I do not think that I have sat in front of the T.V. for more than an hour at a shot since I started playing EQ.<br>
<br>
I think it just boils down to what you want to do with your time...  To me, the boob tube really is a lot less exciting and thought provoking than EQ and cleaning my apt daily has never been something I have done... hehe...<br>
<br>
Oh well...  Live and let Live is what I say.  If they want to take the piece of Life's Pie called EQ and spend it hitting the bars, clubs, dinner parties, T.V. watching, other single player games, etc... then sweet. <p>Myrinia Silverblade<br>
